## Limitations
The findings in this report are based on available literature and may not encompass all societal factors contributing to anorexia. The data is primarily from Western contexts, which may not fully represent global perspectives. Additionally, the complexity of anorexia as a disorder means that societal factors are just one part of a multifaceted issue that includes genetic, psychological, and environmental components.

